The main challenge for citrus farmers has been to get the produce to market as lockdown restrictions hit logistics. The COVID-19 pandemic has not seemed to dent the interest in South Africa’s citrus fruit. Citrus farmers say business is booming. The main challenge for citrus farmers has been to get the produce to market as lockdown restrictions hit logistics. The COVID-19 pandemic has not seemed to dent the interest in South Africa’s citrus fruit. Citrus farmers say business is booming. The main challenge for citrus farmers has been to get the produce to market as lockdown restrictions hit logistics. The COVID-19 pandemic has not seemed to dent the interest in South Africa’s citrus fruit.